valueQuestions.question: Track the trend of average adjusted prices across different neighborhoods over the past year to identify pricing transparency issues and opportunities for dynamic pricing strategies.

feasibility.note: Adjusted prices are in calendar.adjusted_price; neighborhood info in listings or listingsdetails; requires joining calendar with listings, aggregating average adjusted price by neighborhood over time (past year).

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT c.date, l.neighbourhood, ROUND(AVG(c.adjusted_price)::numeric, 2) AS avg_adjusted_price FROM calendar c INNER JOIN listings l ON c.listing_id = l.id WHERE c.date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days' GROUP BY c.date, l.neighbourhood ORDER BY c.date ASC, l.neighbourhood ASC;

valueQuestions.question: List the top-performing neighborhoods by average adjusted price and availability throughout the year to optimize listings for frequent business travelers seeking entire homes or private rooms.

feasibility.note: Requires joining listings or listingsdetails with calendar to get adjusted_price and availability, filtering by room_type (entire homes or private rooms), aggregating by neighbourhood, and ranking neighborhoods by average adjusted price and availability.

valueQuestions.sql:
SELECT l.neighbourhood, ROUND(AVG(c.adjusted_price)::numeric, 2) AS avg_adjusted_price, ROUND(AVG(c.available::int)::numeric, 2) AS avg_availability
FROM listings l
INNER JOIN calendar c ON l.id = c.listing_id
WHERE l.room_type IN ('Entire home/apt', 'Private room')
GROUP BY l.neighbourhood
ORDER BY avg_adjusted_price DESC, avg_availability DESC;

valueQuestions.question: Compare the conversion rates and retention signals between listings with verified hosts and those without to understand the impact of host verification on booking trust and repeat visits.

feasibility.note: Host verification info is in listingsdetails.host_identity_verified; conversion rates and retention signals are not explicitly defined but can be approximated by availability and number_of_reviews or repeat reviews, requiring joins and derived metrics.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT ld.host_identity_verified AS host_verified, ROUND(AVG(ld.availability_365)::numeric, 2) AS avg_availability_365, ROUND(AVG(l.number_of_reviews)::numeric, 2) AS avg_number_of_reviews, ROUND(AVG(l.number_of_reviews_ltm)::numeric, 2) AS avg_number_of_reviews_ltm FROM listingsdetails ld INNER JOIN listings l ON ld.id = l.id GROUP BY ld.host_identity_verified ORDER BY ld.host_identity_verified;

valueQuestions.question: Analyze the trend of number of reviews and review scores over the last 12 months to identify which listings maintain high user engagement and satisfaction for business visitors.

feasibility.note: Number of reviews and review scores exist in listingsdetails and reviewsdetails; requires time filtering for last 12 months and aggregation to analyze trends.

valueQuestions.sql:
SELECT
  DATE_TRUNC('month', rd.date) AS month,
  listingsdetails.id AS listing_id,
  ROUND(COUNT(rd.id)::numeric, 2) AS number_of_reviews,
  ROUND(AVG(listingsdetails.review_scores_rating)::numeric, 2) AS avg_review_score
FROM listingsdetails
INNER JOIN reviewsdetails rd ON listingsdetails.id = rd.listing_id
WHERE rd.date >= (CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '12 months')
GROUP BY month, listingsdetails.id
ORDER BY month, listingsdetails.id;

valueQuestions.question: Compare availability patterns during peak seasons across neighborhoods to identify where limited availability impacts booking opportunities for business travelers.

feasibility.note: Availability patterns by neighborhood require joining calendar with listings or listingsdetails, filtering by peak seasons (time window), and aggregating availability by neighborhood.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT l.neighbourhood, ROUND(AVG(CASE WHEN c.available = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)::numeric, 2) AS avg_availability_rate FROM calendar c INNER JOIN listings l ON c.listing_id = l.id WHERE EXTRACT(MONTH FROM c.date) IN (6, 7, 8, 12) GROUP BY l.neighbourhood ORDER BY avg_availability_rate ASC;

valueQuestions.question: List the top-performing neighborhoods in major cities by occupancy rate over the past year to help property managers optimize listing locations.

feasibility.note: Occupancy rate over past year requires joining calendar and listings/listingsdetails, aggregating availability and bookings by neighborhood and time filtering for last year.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT l.neighbourhood, ROUND((1 - (SUM(CASE WHEN c.available = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)::numeric / COUNT(c.date)::numeric)) * 100, 2) AS occupancy_rate_percentage FROM listings l INNER JOIN calendar c ON l.id = c.listing_id WHERE c.date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days' GROUP BY l.neighbourhood ORDER BY occupancy_rate_percentage DESC LIMIT 10;

valueQuestions.question: List the top-performing neighborhoods in the urban short-term rental market by average occupancy rates over the past year and analyze how occupancy trends vary across these neighborhoods.

feasibility.note: Occupancy rates over the past year can be derived from listingsdetails.estimated_occupancy_l365d (text, likely needs conversion) and calendar data; neighborhood info from listings or listingsdetails. Time series trend requires time-based grouping.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT ld.neighbourhood, c.date, ROUND(AVG(ld.estimated_occupancy_l365d::numeric)::numeric, 2) AS avg_occupancy_rate FROM listingsdetails ld INNER JOIN calendar c ON ld.id = c.listing_id WHERE ld.neighbourhood IS NOT NULL AND c.date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days' GROUP BY ld.neighbourhood, c.date ORDER BY ld.neighbourhood, c.date;

valueQuestions.question: Compare the pricing strategies of hosts with multiple entire home listings versus those with private rooms in terms of adjusted price and occupancy rates to identify optimization opportunities.

feasibility.note: Host listing types (entire home vs private rooms) can be identified from listingsdetails.calculated_host_listings_count_entire_homes and ..._private_rooms. Adjusted price from calendar.adjusted_price. Occupancy rates need derivation or use estimated_occupancy_l365d. Requires joining listingsdetails with calendar and grouping by host and room type.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT ld.host_id, ld.host_name, CASE WHEN ld.calculated_host_listings_count_entire_homes > 0 THEN 'Entire Home' ELSE 'Private Room' END AS listing_type, ROUND(AVG(c.adjusted_price)::numeric, 2) AS avg_adjusted_price, ROUND(AVG(ld.estimated_occupancy_l365d)::numeric, 2) AS avg_occupancy_rate FROM listingsdetails ld INNER JOIN calendar c ON ld.id = c.listing_id WHERE (ld.calculated_host_listings_count_entire_homes > 0 OR ld.calculated_host_listings_count_private_rooms > 0) AND c.available = 't' GROUP BY ld.host_id, ld.host_name, listing_type ORDER BY ld.host_id, listing_type;

valueQuestions.question: List the top-performing neighborhoods by occupancy rate over the past year to help property managers optimize listing locations in the urban rental market.

feasibility.note: Occupancy rate over past year can be derived from calendar.available and listings/neighbourhoods; requires aggregation by neighbourhood and time filtering for last year.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT l.neighbourhood, ROUND((1 - AVG(CASE WHEN c.available = 't' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)::numeric), 2) AS occupancy_rate FROM calendar c INNER JOIN listings l ON c.listing_id = l.id WHERE c.date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days' GROUP BY l.neighbourhood ORDER BY occupancy_rate DESC;

valueQuestions.question: Compare the average adjusted price trends over the last 12 months across different room types to assist hosts in dynamic pricing strategies.

feasibility.note: Adjusted price trends over last 12 months by room_type require aggregation and time filtering on calendar.adjusted_price joined with listings.room_type.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT c.date, l.room_type, ROUND(AVG(c.adjusted_price)::numeric, 2) AS avg_adjusted_price FROM calendar c INNER JOIN listings l ON c.listing_id = l.id WHERE c.date >= CURRENT_DATE - INTERVAL '365 days' GROUP BY c.date, l.room_type ORDER BY c.date, l.room_type;

valueQuestions.question: List the top-performing hosts by estimated annual revenue and their listing counts to identify successful property managers in the mid-sized rental firms segment.

feasibility.note: Estimated annual revenue and listing counts are available in listingsdetails.estimated_revenue_l365d and listingsdetails.calculated_host_listings_count; requires aggregation and ranking by host.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT host_id, host_name, ROUND(SUM(estimated_revenue_l365d)::numeric, 2) AS total_estimated_revenue, ROUND(AVG(calculated_host_listings_count)::numeric, 2) AS avg_listing_count FROM listingsdetails GROUP BY host_id, host_name ORDER BY total_estimated_revenue DESC;

valueQuestions.question: Analyze the distribution of review scores for communication and cleanliness to identify areas where hosts can improve guest satisfaction and retention.

feasibility.note: Review scores for communication and cleanliness are in listingsdetails.review_scores_communication and review_scores_cleanliness; distribution analysis requires aggregation.

valueQuestions.sql: SELECT ROUND("review_scores_communication"::numeric, 2) AS communication_score, ROUND("review_scores_cleanliness"::numeric, 2) AS cleanliness_score, COUNT(*) AS count FROM listingsdetails WHERE "review_scores_communication" IS NOT NULL AND "review_scores_cleanliness" IS NOT NULL GROUP BY communication_score, cleanliness_score ORDER BY communication_score, cleanliness_score;
